node.text: Everyone wants the feeling of freedom, but procrastination can feel like you are caged and can't find the key. We all get stuck in patterns, and the patterns become habits. Procrastination is the same thing.  Procrastination is an action (or non-action) – and it does not define you. Why? It is a habit, that is a behavior pattern that can be changed into a new pattern

node.text:
Accept all of the things in your life that you regret; they happened, and they aren't going to change. What you can embrace and value about them, though, is the ripple effect they have throughout your life. You have learned some important lessons, particularly in these circumstances.Those lessons, based on your experience, are molding you into the person you are now, and will also be the basis from which you give advice to others. 

The wonderful feelings of happiness that good days provide, the intense experiences that bad days bring, the lessons of your worst days, and the memories of your best days are all valuable.  They're shaping you into the person you are and will become. Live every day with absolute gratitude, respect, love and care because this is life and it will test you forever and a day.  Love your life; you are here for a reason.

Give a Heart if you are ready to accept all aspects of your life.
#projecthappiness
#gratituesday
#positivity

node.text:
Life can come at us at times, and there are so many things we cannot control. The difference in forging forward or feeling stuck has a lot to do with the narrative we create around what has happened. In other words, how we INTERPRET the events in our lives. Blaming is natural, often that’s the first way we deal with hurt. But that puts us in more of a victim mode, when our thoughts and fears can seem to take over. But it doesn’t have to be that way.

“The one thing you can’t take away from me is the way I choose to respond to what you do to me. The last of one’s freedoms is to choose one’s attitude in any given circumstance.”― Viktor E. Frankl

That is not to say, deny what you have been through or just shove it under a rock and pretend, “It’s all good.” Feel what you feel, and have some tools to come back to yourself (breathwork, yoga, walking…) When you recognize that the negative ego is constantly giving you messages of doubt and fear, CHOOSE to remind yourself of who you really are: empowered, stronger and always more aware.
#projecthappiness
#mindfulmonday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
"The time to relax is when you don't have time for it." — Sydney J. Harris
It might be tough to find the time to simply relax in today's fast-paced world. What if I told you that relaxing protects your heart, improves your memory, and reduces your chance of stroke? Isn't it possible that you'll be able to fit it into your schedule then? There are so many health benefits of relaxation, and the truth of the matter is that you'll actually improve your productivity and life quality by allowing yourself the time to sit back and do nothing. Mind-wandering has proven benefits, including helping you return to a place where you can access your intuition.

So, if you've been looking for an excuse to ignore all of your responsibilities and spend the day doing nothing but having fun, this is the day for you. Guilt-free. You are the smart one. Taking a break is not only a lovely thing to do for yourself, but it is also a necessary thing to do for yourself. You'll require it. Don’t allow yourself to run on empty. Replenish your energy, ignite your creativity, and remember who you really are.

Challenge: Before you go to sleep, when you are in a relaxed state, ask yourself, or even your higher self, to give you some insights on an issue you are facing. Whether in the shower, or at unexpected moments, be open to receive hints, clues and signs the following day. 
#projecthappiness
#soulsunday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
Real love is not transactional - “I’ll do this for you if you do this for me.” It involves looking through the outer appearances of a person, through their mannerisms, and through the surface affects which really don’t define them. Imagine you had X-ray vision and you can see down to the essence of a person, to their goodness, their vulnerabilities, their hopes and their dreams. 

Love understands that we all carry baggage from the past, and that’s part of being human. And in spite of all that, (and sometimes because of it), we emerge, we shift and we grow. Love is looking for that part, and cheering each other on. As the saying goes, we are all souls in human bodies. When we relate on that level, we cannot help but want the best for one another. Why? We are operating from the frequency of love. 

Send a HEART <3 if you are willing to live more from the frequency of love.
#projecthappiness
#positivity
#socialsaturday

node.text:
We are sometimes surrounded by people who are naturally negative and it can make us feel the same way in their presence. Hurt people tend to hurt people, and they may try to trigger you so you match their energy. Don’t get enmeshed in this toxic dance. If someone is acting out, their ego has taken over; it can get ugly. Be aware that you have choices. You don’t have to stew in the negativity. 

Don’t let their pain kill the beauty in you. 
Don’t let their shame corrode your confidence. 
See things for how they are.
Remember your beauty, resilience and inner strength. 
By calibrating with your true nature, rather than the external noise, you will set yourself free. 
#projecthappiness
#freedomfriday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
Never underestimate the power of a smile. It costs nothing, it means everything and it can literally be the most impactful gift you ever give.  A simple smile plants the seeds for human communion and warm-heartedness. A sincere smile transcends language barriers, it penetrates emotional walls, and cuts through the static of life to bring us closer.  How many of us walk through life, unaware of this ultra powerful vehicle of connection that is so much a part of us that we too often take it for granted? Your smile is your gift - spread it around.

CHALLENGE: Smile at someone new today. You never know the ripple effect.

“It only takes a split second to smile and forget, yet to someone that needed it, that smile can last a lifetime. “-Steve Maraboli 
#projecthappiness
#thoughtfulthursday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
People are like seedlings - we need to be nurtured and connected to nature, and our true nature, to grow. We invest a lot of time cultivating everything else: families, work, friends, and other interests. We look after them, prioritise them, and make time for them. The thing is, we won't flourish if we don't take time for ourselves, our self-care, our relaxation, our mental and physical health. We, through a lack of real effort stay alive, we may even grow but we will not truly thrive or bloom when we don’t take the time and water ourselves and give ourselves what we really need.

When we become a priority, life gets better. We feel better, have more energy and ability to help or support others. We are not pouring from an empty cup, our cup becomes overflowing. When we feel out of sorts, when we feel discomfort or discord there is a reason. Our life is communicating to us. Get curious, it is likely we are not taking the time we need to nurture ourselves. Action needs to be taken. What is it we need? What can we do to feel better? Time appears to be an obstacle, a reason, and an excuse for many people who do not take care of themselves. We all have the same amount of time in a day; the difference is how we prioritise it. If you take the time to water yourself, you will blossom.

Say YES if you are willing to take some time for yourself!
#projecthappiness
#wellnesswednesday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
“There’s nowhere you can be that isn’t where you’re meant to be…” ― John Lennon

Have you noticed when you hope for something, it seldom occurs as you expect? However, the moment you surrender, it makes its way into your life with little worry. When a condition arises that does not match your mental picture, move into your heart and consider the greater lesson contained within the experience.

Trust that life supports your needs and will continue to do so as long as you maintain faith. Tap into your gratitude for your openness, your resourcefulness and your capacity to grow.  Don’t be attached to rigid outcomes. As the saying goes, “Trade your expectation for appreciation.” Life may not unfold how you imagine it, but believe in this benevolent force, regardless. Trust in the language of the heart and know that you are right where you need to be...

Give a Heart if you agree :)
#projecthappiness
#gratituesday
#positivity

"Books train your imagination to think big" - Taylor Swift

However you define yourself, whether you are an adult or a child, being exposed to new worlds, new perspectives, and new adventures blasts opens your mind. You get to walk in another's shoes, experience feelings you might not otherwise access, and grow your sense of what is possible. When you read a book, you make a connection between the events, feelings, experiences, and people in it and yourself. Emotions come alive. We see people trying find a better way of walking through the world, and introducing new ideas to ours.

A book is a gift you can open again and again. - Garrison Keillor

As we celebrate National Book Lovers Day, let us know one book that has touched your life.

#positivity
